    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 81.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Zero-point energy is not bookkeeping \u2014 it is real and measurable. Liquid helium refuses to solidify at any temperature under normal pressure because its zero-point kinetic energy exceeds the binding energy between atoms. The atoms cannot lock into a lattice.",
